---
const pageTitle = "Modernize Automation Without Destabilizing Delivery | QA ALIGN";
const pageDescription =
  "QA ALIGN helps teams modernize test automation safely by improving determinism, diagnosability, and release confidence before scaling complexity.";

  import '../../../styles/components.css';

---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      :root {
        --qa-bg: #0b0e14;
        --qa-panel: #121827;
        --qa-panel-2: #0f1522;
        --qa-text: #e6e9ef;
        --qa-muted: #aab2c5;
        --qa-border: #24304d;
        --qa-link: #7aa2ff;
        --qa-accent: #7aa2ff;
        --qa-accent-2: #9bb8ff;
        --qa-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--qa-bg);
        color: var(--qa-text);
        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      a { color: inherit; }

      .site-shell { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
      .qa-container { width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 2rem)); margin: 0 auto; }

      .qa-section, .qa-hero, .qa-cta-band { margin: 0 0 2rem; }

      .qa-hero, .qa-section, .qa-cta-band__content {
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(18, 24, 39, 0.98), rgba(11, 14, 20, 0.98));
        border-radius: 24px;
        box-shadow: var(--qa-shadow);
      }

      .qa-hero {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
        gap: 2rem;
        padding: 2.25rem;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .qa-section { padding: 2rem; }

      .qa-section--alt {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(15, 21, 34, 0.98), rgba(11, 14, 20, 0.98));
      }

      .qa-section__header {
        max-width: 860px;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }

      .qa-eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
        color: var(--qa-accent-2);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .qa-hero h1, .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
        margin: 0;
        line-height: 1.08;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }

      .qa-hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4rem);
        max-width: 12ch;
      }

      .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
        max-width: 24ch;
      }

      .qa-lead, .qa-copy, .qa-card p, .qa-offer-card, .qa-cta-band p {
        color: var(--qa-muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
      }

      .qa-lead {
        max-width: 62ch;
        margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
        font-size: 1.08rem;
      }

      .qa-copy p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
      .qa-copy p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      .qa-proof-list, .qa-list, .qa-flow {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--qa-text);
      }

      .qa-proof-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
      }

      .qa-list li, .qa-flow li, .qa-proof-list li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

      .qa-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.9rem;
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
      }

      .qa-actions--section { margin-top: 1.5rem; }

      .qa-btn {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 0.82rem 1.15rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 700;
        transition: transform 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
      }

      .qa-btn:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
        border-color: var(--qa-accent);
      }

      .qa-btn--primary {
        color: #08111f;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--qa-accent-2), var(--qa-accent));
        border-color: transparent;
      }

      .qa-btn--secondary {
        color: var(--qa-text);
        background: rgba(122, 162, 255, 0.08);
      }

      .qa-btn--full { width: 100%; }

      .qa-diagram-card, .qa-offer-card, .qa-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        border-radius: 20px;
      }

      .qa-diagram-card { padding: 1.4rem; }

      .qa-diagram-card__eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
        color: var(--qa-accent-2);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      .qa-diagram-card h2 {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      .qa-grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .qa-grid--3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
      .qa-grid--4 { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr)); }

      .qa-card { padding: 1.2rem; }

      .qa-card h3, .qa-offer-card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.3;
      }

      .qa-card p { margin: 0; }

      .qa-two-col {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.7fr;
        gap: 1rem;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .qa-offer-card { padding: 1.35rem; }

      .qa-not-fit {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.75rem;
      }

      .qa-not-fit span {
        display: inline-flex;
        padding: 0.7rem 0.95rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        color: var(--qa-muted);
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content {
        padding: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content h2 {
        max-width: 22ch;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content p {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0.9rem auto 0;
      }

      .qa-cta-band .qa-actions { justify-content: center; }

      @media (max-width: 980px) {
        .qa-hero, .qa-two-col, .qa-grid--3, .qa-grid--4 {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .qa-hero h1, .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
          max-width: none;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .site-shell { padding-top: 1rem; }
        .qa-container { width: min(100% - 1rem, 1180px); }

        .qa-hero, .qa-section, .qa-cta-band__content {
          padding: 1.25rem;
          border-radius: 18px;
        }

        .qa-actions { flex-direction: column; }
        .qa-btn { width: 100%; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="site-shell">
      <div class="qa-container">
        <section class="qa-hero">
          <div class="qa-hero__content">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">QA ALIGN</p>
            <h1>Modernize Automation Without Destabilizing Delivery</h1>
            <p class="qa-lead">
              QA ALIGN helps teams modernize brittle automation systems by fixing trust,
              diagnosability, and state discipline before adding more complexity.
            </p>

            <ul class="qa-proof-list">
              <li>No rewrite-first pressure</li>
              <li>Trust restoration before scale</li>
              <li>Diagnosability before expansion</li>
              <li>Deterministic modernization path</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="qa-actions">
            <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--primary" href="https://buy.stripe.com/eVqcN74vpe5O1Eg86GdAk01">
                Run Your Automation Assessment
            </a>
            <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--secondary" href="/#sprint-6">
                See Sprint Proof
            </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="qa-hero__visual" aria-label="Modernization flow">
            <div class="qa-diagram-card">
              <p class="qa-diagram-card__eyebrow">Modernization Flow</p>
              <h2>Stabilize first, scale second</h2>
              <ol class="qa-flow">
                <li>Identify where trust is breaking down</li>
                <li>Correct state, evidence, and CI signal</li>
                <li>Rebuild confidence in the foundation</li>
                <li>Modernize safely without delivery shock</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">The Core Problem</p>
            <h2>Many automation modernization efforts fail because they try to scale before they stabilize.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-copy">
            <p>
              Teams know the current system is brittle, slow, or hard to trust. But a
              full rewrite often creates more risk, not less. When the foundation is weak,
              adding new tools and new layers can increase instability instead of fixing it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--4">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Legacy pain is real</h3>
              <p>Older suites often carry brittle state, weak contracts, and hard-to-explain failures.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Rewrite pressure is risky</h3>
              <p>Replacing everything at once can destabilize delivery and delay confidence even further.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Tool changes alone do not solve trust</h3>
              <p>Modern frameworks still fail if the underlying architecture remains weak.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Teams need a safer path</h3>
              <p>Progress should improve signal quality, not just create more implementation churn.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">What QA ALIGN Changes</p>
            <h2>Modernize through control, not disruption.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--3">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Deterministic State Discipline</h3>
              <p>Tests start from controlled conditions so the system becomes more predictable before it expands.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Artifact-First Diagnosability</h3>
              <p>Failures become easier to understand, which restores confidence in the automation signal.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>CI Signal Improvement</h3>
              <p>The system is corrected where delivery decisions actually happen, not just in local experiments.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Release Confidence Layer</h3>
              <p>Modernization is tied to clear go / warn / block reasoning instead of surface-level progress reports.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Phased Adoption</h3>
              <p>Changes are introduced in sequence—not all at once.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Architecture Before Hype</h3>
              <p>Trustworthy systems first—not tools, not hype.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">What I Diagnose First</p>
            <h2>The failure patterns that make modernization unstable</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--3">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Shared State and Order Dependence</h3>
              <p>The existing suite relies on execution order or leftover state to behave.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Weak Environment Contracts</h3>
              <p>Tests drift across local, CI, and staging because targeting is not disciplined.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Low-Value Artifacts</h3>
              <p>Failures are hard to explain, making each change more dangerous to introduce.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Framework Change Without System Change</h3>
              <p>The team wants to switch tools, but the real instability lives underneath the framework layer.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>No Release Signal Layer</h3>
              <p>The system runs, but does not give the team a cleaner way to make shipping decisions.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Modernization Scope Creep</h3>
              <p>Too many changes are attempted at once, reducing confidence instead of improving it.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

       <div class="qa-report-sell">
        <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">What You Get</p>
            <h2>What your assessment actually delivers</h2>
            <p class="qa-lead">
            A structured report showing where trust is breaking down, how large the problem is,
            and what it will take to fix it.
            </p>
        </div>
        <p class="report-preview__label">
        Result output — delivered within 24 hours
        </p>

        <div class="report-preview">
             <div class="report-preview__frame">

            <img
            src="/images/assessment-report.png"
            alt="QA Automation Assessment Report preview"
            loading="eager"
            />
            </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="report-points">
        <li>Trust level calculated from your real execution evidence</li>
        <li>Issue patterns identified with occurrence counts</li>
        <li>Cost to stabilize and improve confidence, based on weighted issue patterns</li>
        <li>Before-and-after comparison so you can track improvement over time</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--4">
            <article class="qa-card">
            <h3>Trust Level</h3>
            <p>LOW / MED / HIGH based on real execution evidence.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
